The paper presents a functional intermediate language for verified compilers, which suggests that it falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) category. The language is linear and first-order, which could also place it in the logic in computer science (cs.LO) category. The paper also discusses coherence and register assignment, which are topics related to software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper mentions a nondeterministic environment, which could relate to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Finally, the paper discusses formalization in Coq, which could place it in the architecture (cs.AR) category.
